---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="AI Coding for Open-Ended Survey Responses | Codesift"
  description="Codesift uses AI to categorize open-ended survey responses into codes — faster and more consistent than manual coding."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="article">
        <h1>AI Coding for Open-Ended Survey Responses</h1>

        <p class="lead">
          Manual coding of open-ended survey responses is time-intensive and inconsistent at scale. Codesift uses AI to categorize responses into your defined codes — faster, more consistent, and dramatically more affordable than traditional methods.
        </p>

        <h2>The Traditional Coding Problem</h2>

        <p>
          When you collect open-ended survey responses, you're left with hundreds or thousands of unstructured text answers. To make sense of this data, researchers have traditionally relied on manual coding: reading each response, identifying themes, and assigning categorical codes. This process is essential for analysis, but has several challenges.
        </p>

        <p>
          Manual coding is slow. A single researcher can code 50-100 responses per hour at best. With a dataset of 2,000 responses, you're looking at 20-40 hours of work — and that's after you've developed your codebook. The timeline extends further if you need inter-rater reliability checks or multiple coders.
        </p>

        <p>
          Worse, manual coding becomes inconsistent as the dataset grows. Coder fatigue sets in. Definitions drift. A response coded one way on Monday might be coded differently on Friday. Even with multiple coders and careful documentation, achieving high inter-rater reliability is challenging and adds more time to the process.
        </p>

        <h2>How Codesift Helps</h2>

        <p>
          Codesift brings AI to the coding process without sacrificing control. You define your codes (or allow AI to suggest them) and their criteria — the AI applies them consistently across every response in your dataset. The result is a complete coding pass in minutes, not days, with consistency that doesn't degrade over time.
        </p>

        <p>
          The workflow is straightforward. Upload your survey data. Define your codes with natural-language descriptions: what each code means, keywords, and sample responses that match. Codesift processes your responses and returns coded data ready for analysis.
        </p>

        <p>
          Because the AI follows your definitions exactly, the coding is consistent from the first response to the last. You can refine your codebook and re-code instantly — something that would take hours with manual coding. And unlike automated sentiment tools or topic models, you maintain complete control over the categories.
        </p>

        <h2>Who It's Built For</h2>

        <p>
          Codesift is designed for independent market research consultants, freelance UX researchers, and research teams who need to deliver coded qualitative data quickly and professionally. If you regularly work with open-ended survey questions — customer feedback forms, concept tests, post-interview verbatims, NPS comments — Codesift handles the repetitive coding work so you can focus on insight generation and client deliverables.
        </p>

        <p>
          The pricing model reflects this reality. Traditional auto-coding tools charge per response, making large datasets prohibitively expensive. Codesift charges by data processed — tokens or characters — which typically costs 10-50x less for the same job. A 2,000-response dataset might cost $40-80 with per-response pricing, but only $2-5 with Codesift. The economics finally make sense for consultants working on lean budgets.
        </p>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <h3>Start Coding in Minutes</h3>
          <p>Upload your first dataset and see how fast AI coding can be. No credit card required to start.</p>
          <a href="https://app.codesift.ai" class="btn-primary">Get started free</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div class="related-links">
        <h3>Related resources</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/use-cases/thematic-analysis-for-consultants">Thematic Analysis for Market Research Consultants</a></li>
          <li><a href="/use-cases/qualitative-survey-coding-ai">Qualitative Survey Coding with AI</a></li>
          <li><a href="/compare/manual-vs-ai-coding">Manual vs AI Coding Comparison</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .content-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding-top: 120px;
    padding-bottom: 80px;
  }

  .article {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 42px;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    padding-bottom: 32px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: 48px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .cta-box {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-top: 48px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-box h3 {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .cta-box p {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .related-links {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 48px auto 0;
    padding-top: 32px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .related-links h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .related-links ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .related-links a {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .related-links a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .content-page {
      padding-top: 96px;
      padding-bottom: 60px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 32px;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-top: 36px;
    }

    .cta-box {
      padding: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>
